  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add pine nuts to a pan with a small pinch of salt and pepper. Toast these until browned."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Into a bowl, add the freshly toasted pine nuts, roasted peppers, capers, red chillies, red wine vinegar and 7 tbsp of olive oil. Then season generously with salt and pepper"
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take your coriander seeds and roughly grind them in a mortar and pestle. Then add to your red pepper salsa and mix."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once mixed together, set in the fridge. You want it to be nice and cool before serving."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Next, take your aubergines and place them over an open flame on the hob with a pair of tongs. Turn them regularly until they are charred and collapsed."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the aubergines are cooked, lay them on a plate and cover with another plate for 10 mins. This will make it easier to peel off the skin."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "After 10 mins, remove the skin from the aubergines (don't worry if there are little bits still left on) and add them to your serving plate."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the aubergines down the middle, and spoon in your pepper mix. Pour on some of the juices and top with fresh basil. Tuck in."
    }
  ],
